The government had announced that 2000 health workers would be recruited to help in the fight against COVID-19, the reports say. Nurses have previously complained about poor pay, lack of protective gear, and long working hours. A local news site tweeted photos of nurses at the Queen Elizabeth Central Hospital in the southern city of Blantyre refusing to work. The government announced a 21-day lockdown, starting on Saturday, to curb the spread of COVID-19. The Southern African country has 16 confirmed cases of coronavirus. --BBC--